Package universityProject.dev.dataRepo

Class DataRepository

java.lang.Object
universityProject.dev.dataRepo.DataRepository
public class DataRepository extends Object
Version:
18.12.2023 The DataRepository class manages the storage, retrieval, and manipulation of various entities in the university system. It provides methods for data serialization and deserialization, as well as for pulling and saving data to and from the persistent storage. The class includes vectors for different types of entities, such as employees, students, teachers, etc., and methods for accessing and modifying them. It also manages the user login, logout, and retrieval based on user ID.
Author:
Asyl

    • pullDataFromDatabase

      public static void pullDataFromDatabase()
      Pulls data from the database and populates the static vectors in the DataRepository. This method deserializes data from corresponding files and loads it into the application's memory. It is typically used to initialize or refresh the application's data state from persistent storage.

    • saveTransactionDataToDB

      public static void saveTransactionDataToDB()
      Saves transaction data to the database. This method serializes the current state of the static arrays in the DataRepository and writes them to corresponding files for persistent storage. It is typically used for saving the current state of the application data such as students, teachers, courses, etc., to ensure data consistency and durability.

    • login

      public static universityProject.dev.users.User login(String userName, String password)
      Retrieves the current user of the application. This method searches for a user by their ID in the various vectors like Student, Teacher, Admin, Manager, TechSupportSpecialist. It is useful for identifying the current user based on their unique identifier and obtaining their specific data and permissions.
      Returns:
      User the current user of the application, or null if the user is not found.
